<p>
<h1>Privacy Policy for SchoolMS</h1>

At SchoolMS, we are committed to protecting the privacy and confidentiality of our users' personal information.
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard the data you provide while using our school management system.

<h2>1. Data Collection</h2>

1.1 Personal Information: We may collect personal information such as names, email addresses, 
    phone numbers, and student or parent/guardian details.
    This information is collected voluntarily when users register, update their profiles, or interact with the system.<br />

1.2 Usage Data: We may collect non-personal information about how users interact with our system.
    This includes IP addresses, browser details, device information, and usage statistics.
    This data helps us improve our system and provide a better user experience.

<h2>2. Data Usage</h2>

2.1 System Operation: We use the collected data to operate and maintain our school management system,
    provide requested services, and communicate with users regarding system updates, announcements, and support.<br />

2.2 User Experience Enhancement: We may use the data to personalize user experiences,
    recommend relevant courses or resources,
    and provide targeted information based on user preferences and interests.<br />

2.3 Data Analysis: We may analyze aggregated and anonymized data to gain insights into system usage patterns,
    performance metrics, and trends. This analysis helps us enhance our system and make informed decisions.<br />

2.4 Communication: We may use user-provided contact information to send important notifications,
    newsletters, and updates related to the school management system. Users can opt-out of such communications at any time.

<h2>3. Data Security </h2>

3.1 Data Protection: We implement industry-standard security measures to protect user data from unauthorized access,
    alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes encryption, secure storage, and access controls.<br />

3.2 Data Sharing: We do not sell, rent, or lease user data to third parties.
    We may share data with trusted service providers who assist us in operating the school management system, but they are bound by confidentiality agreements and are not allowed to use the data for other purposes.<br />

3.3 Compliance: We comply with applicable data protection laws and regulations, 
    including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) where applicable.

<h2>4. Data Retention</h2>

    We retain user data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy unless a longer retention period is required by law.
    When data is no longer needed, we securely dispose of it in accordance with our data retention practices.

<h2>5. User Rights</h2>

    Users have the right to access, correct, or delete their personal information stored in our school management system.
    They can update their profile information or contact us to exercise their data rights.

    <h2>6. Updates to the Privacy Policy</h2>

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our data practices or legal requirements.
Users will be notified of any significant updates via email or system notifications.
</p>
